@startuml C4_Pattern_Subnets
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Workflow Pattern - Sub-Net Composition

Boundary(parent, "Parent Net") {
    Component(parent_net, "ParentNet", "Workflow", "Main workflow")
    Component(subnet_task, "SubNetTask", "Task", "Invoke subnet")
}

Boundary(subnet_invocation, "Sub-Net Invocation") {
    Component(subnet_selector, "SubNetSelector", "Logic", "Choose subnet")
    Component(param_mapper_in, "ParameterMapper (In)", "Mapping", "Parent → subnet")
    Component(subnet_context, "SubNetContext", "State", "Execution context")
}

Boundary(subnet, "Sub-Net") {
    Component(subnet_net, "SubNet", "Workflow", "Nested workflow")
    Component(subnet_tasks, "Tasks", "Execution", "Sub-net tasks")
    Component(subnet_completion, "CompletionChecker", "Logic", "Sub-net done?")
}

Boundary(return_path, "Return Path") {
    Component(param_mapper_out, "ParameterMapper (Out)", "Mapping", "Subnet → parent")
    Component(result_handler, "ResultHandler", "Logic", "Return to parent")
}

parent_net --> subnet_task: Invokes
subnet_task --> subnet_selector: Selects subnet
subnet_selector --> param_mapper_in: Maps parameters
param_mapper_in --> subnet_context: Creates context

subnet_context --> subnet_net: Enters
subnet_net --> subnet_tasks: Executes
subnet_tasks --> subnet_completion: Completes
subnet_completion --> param_mapper_out: Maps results
param_mapper_out --> result_handler: Returns
result_handler --> parent_net: Continues

Note as N1
Sub-Net Pattern:
1. Parent invokes sub-net task
2. Select specific sub-net implementation
3. Map input parameters (parent → subnet)
4. Execute sub-net tasks
5. Collect results from sub-net
6. Map output parameters (subnet → parent)
7. Return to parent workflow

Use Cases:
- Code reuse (shared sub-workflows)
- Modular design (encapsulation)
- Exception handlers (alternative flows)
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
